content: Is your Fintype defined as the one in Mathlib 3? If yes, one option is to use whnf on the elements. You will initially hit Quot.mk, and then List.cons and List.nil as you extract the elements. The process can be arbitrarily expensive, you can rely on the default maxHeartbeats or have a more conservative setting option for your procedure.
Yes, it's the binported Fintype from Mathlib 3. Thanks!
Alexander Bentkamp has marked this topic as resolved.
